# 2015-Projects original file manifest (byte-level)

This manifest records the SHA-256 of each original 2015 file in this
repository, computed from the Git object at the historical source commit.
Use this to verify that `archive/2015/README.original.md` and the four
project documents still match byte-for-byte.

- Historical source commit: `dc8e86e7a6aa4f8dab44c381a912b29dd825d085`
- Historical source commit message: `:neckbeard: Added .gitattributes & .gitignore files` (initial), then `add notes`, `add note`, `add a project` for the README + four documents.
- Historical commit date: 2015-01-03 .. 2015-01-12 (UTC, from `git log --pretty='%h %ad %s' --date=short`)

All SHA-256 values below are taken directly from `git cat-file blob <sha>:<path>`
to guarantee they reflect the historical Git object, not the current working tree.

path                            original SHA-256 (from Git object)
